  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed dormers and external staircase, on account of their scale, bulk and siting individually and in combination, would represent incongruous and unsightly additions to the host building, failing to relate to its character and appearance or that of the wider area.  The development would therefore fail to comply with Policy BE1 of the Hillingdon Local Plan: Part One - Strategic Policies (November 2012), Policies DMHB 11 and DMHB 12 of the Hillingdon Local Plan Part Two - Development Management Policies (January 2020), Policy D3 of the London Plan (2021) and Chapter 12 of the National Planning Policy Framework (2021).",
    "The proposal, on account of the addition of dormer windows, would result in a significant increase in perceived overlooking and loss of privacy to the occupiers at No 69 Colham Avenue, to the detriment of the amenities of occupiers and contrary to Policy DMHB 11 of the Hillingdon Local Plan Part Two (2020)."
